Iranian students are ready to die for their country's nuclear program.
They created a living shield.
Several hundred college students have created a living shield around a nuclear facility in Iran.
With their gesture, they want to express support for their country’s nuclear program ahead of a possible Israeli attack.
The students prayed in front of the facility at noon on Tuesday and then called for the deaths of the US and Israel.
Several hundred university students in Isfahan, Iran, created a live shield around the Isfahan Nuclear Technology Center, where uranium is processed.
They show that they are ready to defend their country’s nuclear program with their own lives.
The International Atomic Energy Agency (IAEA) said in a recent report that Iran appears to have continued its pursuit of a nuclear weapon.
There is talk of a possible attack on Iran’s nuclear facilities in Israel.
The students prayed at noon before entering the Isfahan nuclear facility and then shouted death to America and Israel.
In the event of an attack aimed at crippling Iran’s nuclear program as much as possible, the Israeli press said, in addition to the Isfahan center, the target would be a facility in Natanz where uranium is enriched.
The diet of an obese child: does not eat breakfast and dinner sausages
More than a third of children between the ages of 9 and 13 are overweight, with 9 percent of schoolchildren overweight and 5 percent of children obese.
Obese children mostly come from families with unhealthy lifestyles, according to a recent survey.
Once again, it shows how important it is for the healthy development of a person the environment in which he grows up and the patterns with which he is surrounded.
On the tables of obese children, for example, sausages appear up to half more often than in families of children with normal weight.
Fried fries had dinner the day before a research related to an awareness event called Obesity is no more than a coincidence than 19 percent of the obese.
Fatty families are also not used to sports, which is true for most families of today's schoolchildren - only 15 percent of children responded that their parents will find time for active movement at least once a week.
A survey of 900 children
The survey took place at the end of last school year and was attended by almost 900 children from primary schools from all over the Czech Republic.
It was already the second year of the event Obesity is not a coincidence, which is supported by the General Health Insurance Company and Unilever.
So far, more than 12,000 schoolchildren from grades 4 to 8 have been involved in the project.
Eating right and getting enough exercise in the family is one of the determining factors that causes a dramatically increasing number of overweight or even obese children.
“For example, only half of those surveyed said they eat five times a day in the breakfast-snack-lunch-snack-dinner regime, which is one of the basic prerequisites for proper nutrition,” reads one of the survey results.
No breakfast and evening sausages
Experts point out that both relative details, such as regular family breakfast times, are essential for healthy development.
In the Czech Republic, only 23% of schoolchildren eat breakfast at the same time.
In most families, everyone eats breakfast alone.
And the worst thing was finding out that in ten households there is no breakfast at all.
Breakfast is the basis of a proper daily diet.
The questionnaire showed that in families of obese children, unhealthy fries are much more often consumed.
Almost everyone - regardless of weight - drinks sweet lemonades every day (70 percent).
Although more than 40 percent of children regularly participate in sports, the result for their parents was less than half - 15 percent.
Build your own menu
Another part of the survey allowed selected children (204 boys and 172 girls from 13 schools) to create their own diet according to their own taste and opinion.
"The dietary preferences of Czech children aged 12 to 15 years are far from ideal in terms of healthy nutrition."
Among their favorite dishes are a lot of floury, meaty and sweet dishes.
"Apparently, the popularity of sweet lemons is alarming," the survey said in its final report.
For lunch as the main meal, pasta won just above the poultry.
But the children practically did not want legumes at all, and the popularity of fish and midday vegetable dishes is also low.
Adherence to health
At the same time, the survey showed that children are willing to adjust their eating habits if they get the right information.
"The control group of the survey participants who completed the questionnaire after the end of the awareness lecture Obesity is not a coincidence, in many cases there was a significant shift in preferences towards the principles of healthy nutrition," the project's results state.
For example, sweet lemonades were prominent, where more children would begin to prefer plain water.
Children were also much more likely to mark poultry and fish as the main meal of the day in the questionnaire, and would limit sweet foods and dumplings.
Stylist must also be a good psychologist, say professionals
In the introductory article about how stylists learn, I complained a little that there was already a lot in the opening hours.
I had no idea what would happen next.
Lectures by three professionals in the field, dressing problematic characters and a seminar on how it goes on the set.
And it's gonna get worse.
The closer to the final exam, the more information and practical tasks await us.
And even if the course takes place every Saturday and Sunday, it is really "trodden".
This time we discussed with the director Alice (there is not a single boy in the course) how to dress a woman who does not have a perfectly symmetrical figure.
And the vast majority of them are.
Someone has a short neck, someone has a boy figure without proper curves, and someone is overweight.
The stylist must know how to visually soften wide shoulders, lengthen the neck or deliver the necessary curves.
We were given tips on how to emphasize the figure in a woman like Jennifer Lopez, i.e. bigger breasts and hips and a narrow waist, and at the same time not to dress the woman too provocatively.
If, for example, the difference between the waist and the hips is such that the skirt or pants do not really fit, then it is worth having at least one such piece made to measure.
You will not regret it, because the perfect fit of clothes is priceless.
In a tailored skirt you will feel much better than in one that constantly shifts, pulls up, sets off at the waist and the like.
In turn, the boy figure can afford to wear clothes with lashing, applications, embroidery or picking.
Of course, there are a lot of such information and types of characters, so I am glad that I have a whole week to sort out all the information in my head.
And I'm still afraid that given the homework assignment, it's too much.
Each of the students was assigned a celebrity to create two outfits: daytime and evening.
We have to take into account the current appearance, the fashion style of the given personality and the type of character.
I'll "dress" Miranda Kerr, maybe you know her from the Victoria's Secret campaigns.
In the spirit of jubilation, for me personally definitely better than Britney Spears, Christina Aguilera, who recently gained about a hundred kilos (please take into account hyperbole), or young Selena Gomez.
We have to cut the sheets from magazines or search on the Internet and print and then graphically process them.
Moodboard, as the whole result is called, then also expresses our personal style and relationship to graphic design.
Thinking about the graphic aspect of styling is also important.
The stylist does not only dress physically, but also creates, for example, so-called product pages in magazines (for specific tasks, for example, trendy handbags, coats, etc.).
This is what the stylist and designer Mario Kameník told us about.
But not until Sunday.
The stylist must have a general overview
Saturday's lecture, packed with information about the types of characters, was enriched by three guests from the field.
Stylist Honza Pokorný, fashion designer Jakub Polanka and fashion photographer Ben Renč.
Jakub reminded us that fashion is an illusion and a stylist should be able to use it.
And a smart stylist can work with one piece of clothing differently.
Variability is key in this case.
For example, such a trench coat (or if you originally want a trenchcoat) can be worn classically over jeans and a T-shirt as a cloak, but you can also wear it on a bare body, put on pumps and take a picture as a dress.
Or just roll up the sleeves or collar and the whole look looks different.
“Play with it,” he stressed.
But I appreciated the following advice the most: "To work you need to know the rules perfectly."
"Then you can start breaking them," said Jacob.
Finally, it is clear to me why we are crushing all the lessons, what to combine with what, why, when even in fashion magazines we sometimes see something different.
Not to mention the shows.
Thanks to the photographer Ben, I know that the stylist has to have many more variants of clothes than can be photographed.
So for a fashion story that will have ten pages (i.e. ten outfits), I have to be ready to "set up" at least fifteen.
And also that in the photo clothes look and work in combination with other pieces sometimes completely different than in reality.
That is what we have to take into account when creating an outfit.
That the image and style sometimes makes up half of the success, confirmed us Honza Pokorný.
Just look at Madonna, who is not exactly a miraculous singer, but image and marketing have made her a world star.
In the Czech Republic, the approach to the use of stylists is rather cold.
Even the familiar faces sometimes consider it useless (after all, I can do something, the way I look is second-rate).
And if someone has already let us create styling, then we should count on the fact that he will most likely dictate to us a completely different (smaller) size than he really has.
Then all you have to do is google and see if the tabloid has written about the fact that a given celebrity has lost weight and so on.
Both Honza and Mario put it to our hearts on Sunday that it is not enough for a stylist to orient himself in fashion and be able to put together an outfit.
In his work, he primarily communicates with the people he dresses, so it is important to be a good psychologist.
To be able to judge people, not to pander, to stand up for your opinion.
“When a manager orders you to sort through her wardrobe and fill it with nice pieces, you can’t throw out the whole closet and say, for God’s sake, that’s terrible.”
"Find at least a few things to praise and recommend what they can be worn for," says Mario.
He also showed us specifically what the so-called "place" or bag for the place must contain.
It’s the one that you fasten around your waist and you have all the necessary props with you.
In addition to clear things, such as scissors, hair roller or closing pins, there are also nylon thread (with it the stylist helps when taking photos of products, such as handbags or hats), special clips, with which we fasten the back of clothes, if it is larger (pin or other clamp are not allowed, they would damage the clothes), or sew.
In order not only to listen, but also to try something practical, we learned how to properly catch shoes.
Even when shooting in a studio where there is a flat surface, the sole could be damaged, let alone outside.
And so we glued and glued.
Do not touch the shoes with scissors, so that they do not accidentally damage.
So you really need skill.
Mario pleased me when he praised my creation without reservation.
This skill is not really my friend.
This is just a small fraction of what we heard about the second weekend of the course.
It is becoming more and more clear to me that it is not really a walk in the park, no matter who says what.
Need for Speed: The Run races across America.
Reviews
The originally carefree ride turns into a routine morning commute due to a series of completely unnecessary sloppy mistakes.
The ambition has been largely fulfilled, but it is of no use if no one clearly wanted to do anything extra.
The new episode, subtitled The Run, had high expectations for the release.
He promised to move the long-running racing series Need for Speed in a new direction, and from the playable examples it seemed like a game that would not be only in the genre of action racing.
We were also curious how the inserted passages will turn out, in which the main character will get out of the car and run on his own.
However, as is usual with the NFS series, many are in the end a little different than we expected.
These are potentially decent arcade races, but the whole pulls down a few unnecessary bugs that have been appearing in the series for more or less several years.
So they are not actually mistakes, but rather a manifestation of some incomprehensible laziness of developers.
The adventure starts very well.
You are introduced to a story whose main character Jack has certain problems of a personal nature and as a solution is offered to participate in an illegal race across America.
Get behind the wheel on the west coast of San Francisco and your mission is to be the first to arrive in New York.
The idea has some interesting elements.
The route is divided into ten stages, and then more than fifty races.
It follows that each race is on a different track and the stages are set in different, sufficiently different and interesting environments.
You don’t feel like the game is always the same.
In addition, some of the environments are very nice to look at, although the technical level of graphics corresponds to the previous works of the series.
So it's nothing world-shattering.
But driving through the desert, autumn landscape or high in the snowy mountains looks very pleasant visually.
From time to time, the race is filled with an unusual element.
In the desert, for example, you get caught in a sandstorm, which significantly reduces visibility.
On the other hand, in the mountains, you have to be careful not to be overwhelmed by an avalanche.
In addition, the individual races are quite well seeded behind each other.
There are only a few types, but that’s enough.
For a while you try to pass the required number of opponents (basically a classic race), then you catch up again (classic fight with stopwatches) and then you are waiting for a duel with a single opponent.
From time to time, even the police will get involved, making all your efforts even more unpleasant.
New is the passage outside the car.
It's more about such interactive animations, when Jack usually runs away from someone and you have to help him in this by pressing the right buttons at the right moments.
Nothing complicated.
However, it is surprising that there are far fewer of these passages in the game than you would expect (in particular, perhaps only three).
In the end, however, it is to the benefit of the matter, because this element does not have a chance to become annoying and in the context of the above, it ranks among the elements that diversify the game.
The ride model follows in the footsteps of the previous parts.
That is, it is definitely not who knows anymore, but it can not be said that it is a negative.
If you’re looking for a realistic simulation, you’ll need to look elsewhere.
But the more action-packed racing still suits the model quite well, although we could find a better one in the competition.
So far so good.
Problems begin to arise after a while.
Unlike the road model, the model is no longer in good condition.
We do not expect it to count complex deformations and collisions, but if you have no idea how your car will behave before almost any impact on any object, then everything is probably not quite right.
Typically, with close overtaking or passing cars in normal traffic, sometimes you just lick each other lightly, but other times in an almost identical situation your car ends up in wild pirouettes.
Or even to attack.
Thanks to the restart system, it does not matter, but it will tune you up reliably.
Restarts are designed in such a way that if you break down or drive far off the track, the game will throw you back to the last stop on the track.
However, only five restarts are available in each race.
When you run out of them, you have to start the race again from the beginning.
This is more of an aid in case something goes wrong than you can rely on them.
Sometimes, however, even restarts do not help, they are solved only by the need to learn a given section of the race by heart.
The big problem with this game is that the same things often happen in the same places.
Some corners, for example, need to be driven in a specific way, otherwise you will simply not fit into them.
Other times you will meet "civilian" cars in the same configuration, whether you arrive there first, fifth, five seconds earlier or a minute later.
This is especially annoying in situations where you see an opponent pass easily between two oncoming cars, while when you get there, the cars are already in such a position that you have to go around them or slow them down.
It does not matter when you reach them, because it is "calculated" so that the situation always occurs right in front of your nose.
Competitors have another advantage.
Throughout the game, you will come across several places where, again, regardless of time, you will always be overtaken by the same opponent in the same place.
At the end of the game on the long bridge, where you drive in the opposite direction.
The enemy must get there in front of you, apparently, at any cost.
When it is in front of you, it makes your view of the oncoming cars worse, so you will probably spread out a few times at first.
It is possible to understand the intention to make the game more exciting and adrenaline, but the execution is so obvious that it will reliably disgust you quickly.
And it's a shame, because despite a simple driving model, playing is fun and sometimes so action-packed that sometimes you literally do not have time to watch where what flies.
And it doesn’t really matter if it’s a concept with fifty unique tracks, sorting the races so that boredom doesn’t have a chance, or anything else.
An unusual idea is to change cars during races.
You have to watch out for gas pumps near the roads, because you can change the car there, although in the vast majority of cases you can do with what you have.
Cars are divided into three categories.
Sports cars are suitable for urban areas, strong American roadblocks on straight highways and exotic supersports on technical riding, for example, on winding mountain roads.
The main story mode goes hand in hand with the challenge mode, which are races in individual locations that you know from the story.
Here you get not only medals, but also experience points to your profile, which is common for challenges and story.
To get a higher level of the driver, various items are unlocked: starting with cars and ending with backgrounds for the profile.
It is also connected to the online Autolog function, which compares your achievements with other players and provides other community functions.
One of the more difficult to understand kicks is the situation from the last race in the story.
With your car you will get to the subway tunnel (be) where you will drive it in the dark on the tracks (be).
On the tachometer you flash numbers between 150 and 200 km / h (let it be) and in this comes a metro set from the back and uncompromisingly scraps you.
In the editorial office, we will probably have a few more days of discussions about whether no one really thought a bit about creating the game, or whether the authors consider us to be such a big idiot.
The technical side of the game is nothing special, but at least the overall visual impression is in most cases very pleasant and in some cases even great.
It freezes so that in some more tense moments the shooting decreases, and in some cases quite tragically.
However, this applies especially to a crash with a larger number of participants, when smooth shooting would not be useful for you anyway.
The sound is fine and the soundtrack is a matter of taste.
In an effort to appeal to the widest possible range of a rather younger audience, a soundtrack from the category "every dog different village" was created, but it can be assumed that for the sake of listening to music, someone will probably not buy the game.
Need for Speed: The Run is so good.
If the game avoided completely unnecessary mistakes, then we would not be afraid to say that The Run is the best work of NFS in the last few years.
This is how the game feels unfinished.
Fun is definitely good, but be prepared for the fact that the mistakes will smack you in the eye with the power of airport spotlights.
UK choirs will perform at the concert Students of Velvet
This is the third time Festa Academica has combined the celebrations of International Student Day and the anniversary of the Velvet Revolution with a musical experience.
During it, twenty high school and university choirs will be introduced.
The main focus of the festival are two concerts held on November 17.
"Charles University has a big stake in the festival".
"Among the participating choirs is the Choir of the Faculty of Education and the Faculty of Humanities, Rector Václav Hampl will sit on the festival committee," said Jakub Čaloun, head of the organizing team.
The highlight of the whole festival is a free concert of high school choirs, which will take place on November 17 at 2 pm in front of the National Technical Library in Dejvice.
The program includes a composition by the prominent Czech jazzman Karel Růžička Celebration Jazz Mass.
In the evening, a concert "Students of Velvet" will take place in the ceremonial premises of the National House in Vinohrady, where university choirs, including the choirs of Charles University, will perform.
Festa Academica aims not only to celebrate International Student Day with dignity and to commemorate the 22nd anniversary of the Velvet Revolution, but also to present choral music to the public at the highest level and to develop the creative cooperation of young people.
The main organizer is the Union of Czech Choirs in cooperation with the Jan Kepler Grammar School.
Mayor of Prague Bohuslav Svoboda and Rector of Charles University Václav Hampl took over the whole event.
The festival will take place from 16 to 20 November in Prague and Pardubice.
In addition to festive concerts, the schedule also offers a variety of musical meetings, student happenings, matinees and other programs.
Detailed information can be found on the festival website www.festaacademica.cz
Ambassador to the European Union Vice-President:
Czechs have a reputation for being negative and Eurosceptic
"The Lisbon Treaty has significantly upset the balance between the various institutions."
"I didn't expect it to be such a hard war."
"It will take five or six years for the situation to settle down, calm down and for all players to get used to their new roles," Czech Ambassador to the European Union Milena Vicenová began her lecture at the Faculty of Law.
To what extent she takes her motto "Comprehensively and openly about Europe" seriously, she showed in the first part of the lecture, when she managed to describe individual EU institutions and their relations in such a clear and understandable way that many lecturers from the Faculty of Law of the Charles University could envy her.
Vicenová also commended the work of the new permanent President of the European Council, Herman Van Rompuy:
"At first, there was criticism that he was indistinct, that he was a grey official, that he could not play any role, and I have to say that everyone was out of breath, that he played the role very well."
"He is a man who can listen to the 27 Member States, communicate well with them and has a clear vision of where the European Union should go."
She then explained the new post of High Representative for Foreign Affairs and Security Policy as an answer to the question: "Who is the European Union? Which phone number should I call?", i.e. as an important step towards unifying and making the EU's policy towards countries such as China or India more readable.
No one wants to ban mermaids.
Vicenová also addressed the agenda that the European Council has lived, will live and will live on in the near future.
The Czech Presidency last year was a success.
The Czechs have solved the coming financial crisis, solved the gas crisis or organized a summit for the Eastern Partnership.
The fall of the government at that time was a big negative, which greatly damaged the Czech Republic.
The Czech representation in the EU is currently very busy.
In the words of the Ambassador, the "fact" was not only the Presidency, but also the subsequent financial crisis, which is still being addressed today.
In addition, the new seven-year budget of the Union has yet to be approved, which is becoming much more complicated due to the current economic situation.
Whether the budget will be slim and economical, which sectors will be given priority, which countries will be supported more and which will be less, is all on the agenda of the next negotiations.
The ambassador also recalled her main slogans, with which she came to Brussels: "About Europe in a comprehensible way".
"I really don't like nasty shortcuts, foreign words, slang that no one understands.
How can a citizen understand that in Brussels we don’t really invent curvy or round cucumbers, bananas of various sizes, or that we really have to be banned from cheesecakes?”
It also wants to make better use of the EU environment and get more Czechs into European institutions.
We have a multi-speed Europe.
According to the ambassador, the Czechs have a reputation for Eurosceptics and people who notice the negative rather than the positive aspects of the matter.
Moreover, it regrets the low representation of Czechs in European institutions.
According to her, many factors are to blame, such as the modesty of our candidates, their inability to write motivation letters, but also low support from the Czech side.
In addition to the successful Czech Presidency, she highlighted the strength and cooperation of the Visegrad Four.
"Believe me, when a Pole and a Hungarian come to me and a Slovak approaches, the Frenchman next to me says: 'Hey, what are you guys doing there, what about your Visegrad four?' and he doesn't look excited about it at all."
In the future, Vicenová said, the EU is mainly waiting for new tough rules for the budgetary policies of member states.
He sees the concept of a two-speed, if not multi-speed Europe as very real, rather than a new "European federation."
“We have eurozone countries and countries outside the eurozone.”
"We have the Schengen area, we have the Institute of Enhanced Cooperation."
"For the first time, it was said that only the countries that want to work together and those that don't want to stand by."
"There will be more of these institutes and it will be a strongly two-speed Europe," Vicenová said.
In this respect, it also praised the role of the Czech Republic and Herman Van Rompuy in promoting the principle that all issues that have an impact on the entire Union should be discussed between all Member States, not only between the countries of the euro area.
Brand story:
IBM Innovator Begins His Second Century
If someone were looking for the word that most accurately expresses IBM's strategy, the closest would probably be "long-term".
For the general public, IBM is a symbol of the technological revolution, it is a company perceived as very contemporary, and yet it has been a hundred years since its foundation.
The foundation for this long-term commitment was laid by the company’s first CEO, visionary Thomas J. Watson Sr.
He has already coined the slogan that many of the world’s problems can be easily solved if people are willing to think.
His slogan "Think!" became the imprint around which the life of the future giant will unfold (and also the name of an internal magazine, which began to be published at IBM in 1935).
It was also the foundation of Watson's carefully built corporate culture.
“For us at IBM, long-term thinking is a continuous movement toward the future.
IBM survived and prospered for a hundred years because it remained true to its core values and was not afraid to change everything around it.
This allowed us to transform technology, business and society during our first century.
We hope to achieve even more in the second hundred,” said Samuel J. Palmisano, the company’s current CEO.
A sophisticated system
In the 1930s, Watson approached the care of his employees in a similar way as the entrepreneur Bata in the Czech Republic - IBM people were among the first American employees to have paid holidays, insurance from an employer plus an elegant employee uniform and an elaborate system for rewarding the best inventors and businessmen.
IBM also has a long-term customer relationship.
