How to recognize a lie
A glance at recent headlines suggests how serious and pervasive lies and deceptions are in everyday life.
Republican presidential candidate Herman Cain has his hands full with allegations that he sexually harassed several women - both sides claiming the other is lying.
Administrators at Penn State University were charged with perjury when they tried to hide records of a retired football coach sexually assaulting a boy.
