The French are no more sick than elsewhere in Europe.
Let’s start with a few official numbers.
According to the Caisse nationale d'assurance maladie (CNAM), more than 237 million euros of daily compensation was paid in 2006.
According to the French Institute for Research and Documentation in Health Care, in 2008, daily compensations of 11.3 billion euros accounted for 5% of health care expenditures.
